con:interface.name: Quoting related parts of Open API for FSP Interoperability (FSPIOP) (Implementation Friendly Version)
con:interface.con:description: Based on API Definition.docx updated on 2018-03-13 Version 1.0. Note - The API supports a maximum size of 65536 bytes (64 Kilobytes) in the HTTP header.

con:method.name: BulkQuotes
con:method.con:description: The HTTP request POST /bulkQuotes is used to request the creation of a bulk quote for the provided financial transactions in the server. BulkQuotes

con:parameter.con:name: accept
con:parameter.con:description: The Accept header field indicates the version of the API the client would like the server to use.

con:parameter.con:name: content-length
con:parameter.con:description: The Content-Length header field indicates the anticipated size of the payload body. Only sent if there is a body. Note - The API supports a maximum size of 5242880 bytes (5 Megabytes)

con:parameter.con:name: content-type
con:parameter.con:description: The Content-Type header indicates the specific version of the API used to send the payload body.

con:parameter.con:name: date
con:parameter.con:description: The Date header field indicates the date when the request was sent.

con:parameter.con:name: x-forwarded-for
con:parameter.con:description: The X-Forwarded-For header field is an unofficially accepted standard used for informational purposes of the originating client IP address, as a request might pass multiple proxies, firewalls, and so on. Multiple X-Forwarded-For values as in the example shown here should be expected and supported by implementers of the API. Note - An alternative to X-Forwarded-For is defined in RFC 7239. However, to this point RFC 7239 is less-used and supported than X-Forwarded-For.

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-source
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-Source header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for identifying the sender of the HTTP request. The field should be set by the original sender of the request. Required for routing and signature verification (see header field FSPIOP-Signature).

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-destination
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-Destination header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for HTTP header based routing of requests and responses to the destination. The field should be set by the original sender of the request (if known), so that any entities between the client and the server do not need to parse the payload for routing purposes.

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-encryption
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-Encryption header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for applying end-to-end encryption of the request.

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-signature
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-Signature header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for applying an end-to-end request signature.

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-uri
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-URI header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for signature verification, should contain the service URI. Required if signature verification is used, for more information see API Signature document.

con:parameter.con:name: fspiop-http-method
con:parameter.con:description: The FSPIOP-HTTP-Method header field is a non-HTTP standard field used by the API for signature verification, should contain the service HTTP method. Required if signature verification is used, for more information see API Signature document.

con:method.name: BulkQuotesByID
con:method.con:description: The HTTP request GET /bulkQuotes/<ID> is used to get information regarding an earlier created or requested bulk quote. The <ID> in the URI should contain the bulkQuoteId that was used for the creation of the bulk quote. BulkQuotesByID

con:parameter.con:name: accept
con:parameter.con:description: The Accept header field indicates the version of the API the client would like the server to use.

con:method.name: BulkQuotesByID1
con:method.con:description: The callback PUT /bulkQuotes/<ID> is used to inform the client of a requested or created bulk quote. The <ID> in the URI should contain the bulkQuoteId that was used for the creation of the bulk quote, or the <ID> that was used in the GET /bulkQuotes/<ID>. BulkQuotesByID

con:parameter.con:name: content-length
con:parameter.con:description: The Content-Length header field indicates the anticipated size of the payload body. Only sent if there is a body. Note - The API supports a maximum size of 5242880 bytes (5 Megabytes)

con:method.name: BulkQuotesErrorByID
con:method.con:description: If the server is unable to find or create a bulk quote, or another processing error occurs, the error callback PUT /bulkQuotes/<ID>/error is used. The <ID> in the URI should contain the bulkQuoteId that was used for the creation of the bulk quote, or the <ID> that was used in the GET /bulkQuotes/<ID>. BulkQuotesErrorByID
